cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.SC

This paper deals with dictionary learning, which is a common technique in machine learning and computer vision. The use of singular value decomposition and sparse representations suggests that the paper may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The implementation of the algorithm on a GPU suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of sparse representations and computer vision applications suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The numerical results and optimization techniques suggest that it may also fall under the category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Languages).
